Base64 encoding
 - It is used to make life easier for us when we want to tranmit data in binary - > instead it converts 6 digit binary to a single digit.

to encode something in ubuntu

echo -n [filname or text] | base64

to decode something in ubuntu

echo [filename or text] | base64 -d

URL encoding
 It is also known as percent encoding, when we want to trasmit /, ?, or = over the network. These characters lie out side the ASCII characters set.
 e.g the space character is transmitted as %20 or +. 
 ` = 	%80	 or %E2%82%AC
 

 
